                <h5>Diamonds – Now Certified</h5>
                <p>The simple answer is, with certifications. Today, diamond jewellery always comes with a certificate that states how many diamonds are in the piece of jewellery, what the weight, colour grade or clarity rating of each diamond is, as well as details on how the diamonds have been set. Certifications have been used for mined diamonds for several years now, providing people with proof that their diamond has been graded and classified by an expert gemmologist and that they are receiving exactly what they have asked for. Additionally, these certificates also spoke about the ‘origin’ of the mined diamond. This was done specifically to assure people that their diamonds were conflict-free and were not a product of the blood diamond trade.</p>
                    <h5>Certifications for Lab-Grown Diamonds</h5>
                    <p>Even though the origins of lab-grown diamonds are not being questioned, these engineered diamonds also require some form of certification to prove their authenticity. The certificates provided with lab-grown diamond jewellery assure you that your diamonds have been graded by expert gemmologists and that they are the same cut, colour, clarity and weight that you have asked and paid for.
